parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including faulty warning lights, malfunctioning accessories, and even fires, which can pose a significant risk to vehicle safety and occupant well-being.
symptoms: Dashboard lights failing to illuminate
high-beam headlights turning off and on independently
passenger's side air bag warning light illumination
electrical fires
and faulty warning indicators.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the liftgate actuator can prevent the rear door from locking or unlocking, creating a safety concern in emergency situations, particularly for passengers in the third row.
symptoms: Liftgate failing to open or lock
inability to unlock the door or window from the inside
and lack of manual release for the liftgate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Instrument Cluster and Warning Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty instrument clusters and warning lights can lead to confusion and distraction while driving, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent warning lights
faulty fuel gauges
and service tire pressure warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Key Fob Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty ignition switches and key fobs can cause difficulties in starting or turning off the vehicle, leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: Key becoming stuck in the ignition switch
inability to turn the vehicle off
and faulty key fob operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning HVAC systems can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Heater shorting out
causing electrical fires
and faulty blower motor resistors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of brake pedal pressure can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded, as the vehicle may not stop properly.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate/hatch can trap passengers inside the vehicle, especially in emergency situations, and pose a significant safety risk.
symptoms: The rear liftgate/hatch will not open
the rear liftgate/hatch will not unlock
the rear window will not open
there is no manual or key-operated way to unlock the rear liftgate/hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rattling of the body and frame can cause a loss of control while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The body and frame of the vehicle are rattling loudly
the truck shakes heavily while braking
causing a temporary loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate locking mechanism can cause the liftgate to become stuck in a locked position, making it difficult or impossible to open, which can lead to safety risks in emergency situations.
symptoms: The rear liftgate fails to unlock
the liftgate cannot be opened manually or automatically
the keyless entry system fails to unlock the liftgate
the liftgate window fails to open
the liftgate is stuck in a locked position
and there is no manual way to open the liftgate from the inside or outside of the vehicle.
